<p>Router placement should be planned at the same time. A terminal may work well outside while the Wi-Fi inside performs poorly because the router is hidden in a corner. Place the router near the main usage area or use mesh devices to extend coverage. For large homes, plan coverage for bedrooms, living room, kitchen, study, home office, servant quarter, balcony, and outdoor sitting areas where needed.</p>

